Last checking has been done.
Thorium and uranium targets of about 1 mg/cm**2
thickness were electrodeposited from Th(NO3)4*5H(2)O
and UO(2)(NO3)2*6H(2)O aqueous solutions onto
beryllium and aluminum foils, respectively.
Each stack consisted of 2 and 5 target foils. 10 mg/
cm**2 thick copper foils were inserted down stream of
the target stack.

x4freetext: The nuclear data used for
analyses were taken from this work.
.Statistical model calculations.
Angular momentum (L) effects on mass yield curves were
studied for the fission from the same compound nucleus
Np-239 of the same excitation energy but with different
angular momenta, produced by the Li-7+Th-232 and U-238+
reactions.
For 47 and 40-MeV Li-7(3+) beams.
The 35-MeV proton beam was delivered by
the sf-cyclotron of ins.
The 40-MeV proton beam was delivered by
the cyclotron of cyric.
Beam currents were about 160 electrical
nanoampere for Li-7 and 650 nanoamperes for the
protons.
Reaction products were identified through their
characteristic gamma-rays and half-lives.
The uncertainty in the determination of cross
sections was estimated to be 5-10% based on that
associated with counting statistics, photon abundance
(1-10%) and gamma-ray detection efficiency  (about 5%)
.The excitation energy of the compound nucleus
as calculated by authors.
- By authors - all `EN` in data sections are beam
energy at the center of each target.
